    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-24T13:00:00-05:00" n="1005"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1005">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.797/15: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 24, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>202. Your 247, December 19, 5 p.m.</p>
                <pb facs="1164" n="1052" xml:id="pg_1052"/>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>The Department has no objection to exploratory conversations with Kurusu
                        in regard to details of the draft legislation.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>While leaving the matter to the Embassy’s judgment, the Department
                        inclines to the opinion that, if the proposed legislation conforms to the
                        Embassy’s 1440, August 22,<note n="21" xml:id="d1005fn21">Not
                            printed.</note> an oral statement as authorized in the final paragraph
                        of the Department’s 882, November 18, would be desirable.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
